                                                                                                               PM trip to London
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, March 9: Prime Minister Manmohan Singh is likely to attend the April 2 G20 summit in London, sources said. He is expected to leave Delhi on April 1 and return two days later.        
	A final decision is yet to be taken, but the sources said the Prime Minister would not want to miss an important meeting of world leaders amid a global economic crisis.        
	British Prime Minister Gordon Brown, the host, is keen that Singh attend the conference, the sources said.        
	Singh might also get an opportunity to hold his first bilateral meeting with US President Barack Obama on the sidelines of the summit. The US President and the Prime Minister will have many issues to discuss. The regional issues  Afghanistan, Sri Lanka and Pakistan  and the issue of terrorism, a source said.                                                                                                                                                                            
